The Chronicle Mashudu Netsianda, Senior Reporter ZANU-PF Secretary for Transport and Welfare Cde July Moyo said the party has allocated each district a bus to ferry delegates to its 17th Annual National People’s Conference in Esigodini in Matabeleland South province. The buses will be inspected by the Vehicle Inspectorate Department to make sure they are roadworthy. The serious business of the conference begins with a Politburo meeting on Tuesday at the party’s headquarters in Harare followed by that of the Central Committee at the same venue on Wednesday On Thursday, delegates travel to the venue for the official opening of the conference on Friday by the party’s First Secretary and President, Cde Emmerson Mnangagwa. More to follow…